Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Conservative Political Action Conference (CPAC) in which he addressed the recent school shooting in Parkland, Florida, and emphasized the administration's commitment to making schools safer and addressing mental illness. He also highlighted the accomplishments of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, deregulation, and strong leadership on the world stage. Pence urged members of the conservative movement to continue their support and work towards victory in the upcoming congressional elections. He also encouraged Americans to reconnect with each other and their communities, and to have faith in the future of the country. Pence closed his speech by invoking the words of the late Reverend Billy Graham and emphasizing the importance of prayer and hope in healing the nation.